    <description>Fast play air-to-air combat miniatures game for jets equipped with guns and missiles. The game uses a rectangular grid with playing card suits marking 4 rows and cards K to A marking 14 columns, similar to Gary Graber's G&amp;ouml;ring's War.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Jets have individual flight characteristics for vertical and lateral movement, as well as armament and structural points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn a card is drawn for each jet to place it onto the grid on the appropriate space. Jets may be able to move to a different space by drawing a new card that must be lower than its movement rating. Thereafter shooting cannon fire and missiles is preformed in a similar fashion. At the end of each turn, the jets are removed from the grid, so may reappear on an entirely new angle of attack the following turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules provide many optional rules and complete aircraft statistics for any period from the Korean War to present.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A short introduction to the rules, focusing on the Vietnam era, is available in Wargames Illustrated No. 254 (December 2008), under the name &amp;quot;Very Instant Thunder&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
